results.name: Permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A268674(A269379(n)).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
example: For n=9 we first find what number is below 9 in square array A255127, which is 19, then we find what number is above 19 in square array A083221, which is 17, thus a(9) = 17.
xref: More recursed variant: A269358. Cf. also permutations A266646, A255408, A269172.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Mar 03 2016
